NIGERIAN songstress Temilade Openiyi aka Tems has explained why she creates her kind of sound and song without losing her essence. Tems made this known in episode two of her podcast on Apple radio entitled Leading Vibe Radio.   It’s my turn to shutdown 02 Arena – Uzo     Kemi Oyedeji speaks on new book, ushering     I’m happy to be back after 10 years, says Shan George   The 26-year-old singer said, “Some people’s way of creating is thinking about the masses. That’s perfectly fine. But for me and for any real artist, if you want to be happy because you can have all the money in the world, you can have all the hits in the world and you’ll be miserable and you’ll be trapped because you now start feeling like you can’t express the real you after making so many hits. Then you can’t, you’re afraid to show people who you actually are. Because you feel they won’t accept you. And then you trap yourself in your mind and you live your life continuously miserable.” The RCA signee became a global star after collaborating with Wizkid on ‘Essence,’ one of the songs from his 2021 album, ‘Made in Lagos.’